              IssuanceSpec issuanceSpec,
              java.math.BigInteger pseudonym,
              DomNym theDomNym,
              Values theValues)
Create an Issuer, to issuer a credential to a Recipient.

Parameters:
issuerKey - The issuer's public and private key.
issuanceSpec - Issuance specification, describing what will be in the credential and how it will be issued.
pseudonym - Pseudonym (optional).
theDomNym - Domain pseudonym (optional).
theValues - Values known to the issuer.

round2

public final Message round2(Message msg)
The main functionality of the Issuer. Once initialized, the Issuer receives a message from the Recipient, and computes a response, consisting of the CL signature, and proof that it was correctly computed.

Parameters:
msg - the first flow of the protocol; a message from the Recipient.
Returns:
a response to the Recipient.

getIssuerUpdateInformation

public final IssuerUpdateInformation getIssuerUpdateInformation()
Returns:

updateCredential

public static Message updateCredential(IssuerKeyPair issuerKeyPair,
                                       Values values,
                                       IssuerUpdateInformation issuerRecord)
Updates a credential to the given values using the information from the issuer record.

Parameters:
issuerKeyPair - Key pair to be used.
values - New values of known attributes (only a subset of the known attributes might be updated).
issuerRecord - Issuer record containing the old attribute values as well as the required signature elements to update the signature.
